{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ReRYb4MZ6TG9tMz5zp6q65","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive picture of all the non-default settings:\n\n1. **Log verbosity**: Set to `1` (default is `0`)\n2. **Slow operation threshold**: Set to `200ms` (default is `100ms`)\n3. **Operation profiling mode**: Set to `slowOp` (mode 1) (default is `off`, mode 0)\n4. **Journal compressor**: Set to `zlib` (default is `snappy` for WiredTiger)\n\nThe replica set configuration (`rs.conf()`) looks standard - all members have equal priority of 1, no hidden members, no delays, etc. There's nothing non-default there.\nFor the rollback, I need to reset these settings: I can adjust log verbosity, the slow operation threshold, and profiling mode through runtime commands, but the journal compressor change requires modifying the config file and restarting the server since that parameter can't be adjusted while the database is running. ity and profiling are runtime-changeable, so I can apply those immediately to each pod without waiting for a restart. The journal compressor change requires a rolling restart since it's a storage-level setting. I'm thinking through whether the rollback script should update the ConfigMap first, then apply runtime changes, then trigger the restart, or handle it in a different order. Writing the rollback script... Writing shell commands... Writing verification commands...\n\nActually, I'm realizing the ConfigMap patch needs proper YAML formatting with escaped newlines when using JSON patch syntax.  Let me reconsider using a cleaner approach with a here-doc and `kubectl apply` instead, which handles the multiline config file more naturally without escaping issues. Writing the rollback script...\n\nI need to think through the full sequence: the ConfigMap update removes the profiling settings and reverts the journal compressor, then I'll reset the runtime settings on each pod to turn off profiling mode and restore default thresholds, followed by a rolling restart so MongoDB picks up the config file changes. Writing the rollback script... Writing shell commands... Writing verification commands...\n\nI need to save this script to a file first, then create the ConfigMap from it without executing the rollback itself—just storing it for review.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":288,"cache_read_input_tokens":34698,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":288},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c7af558-bf73-44d4-a74b-4537dca6c47c","uuid":"08211457-c169-4014-9eb2-97eeacb56f04","request_id":"req_011CcMYbwivYNvXfDu7JHy3V"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ReRYb4MZ6TG9tMz5zp6q65","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"I now have a complete picture of all non-default settings. Let me summarize what was found and write the rollback script.\n\n**Non-default settings detected:**\n- `systemLog.verbosity: 1` (default: 0)\n- `operationProfiling.mode: slowOp` (default: off)\n- `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs: 200` (default: 100)\n- `storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor: zlib` (default: snappy)\n- Replica set config itself is all-default (equal priority members, no hidden/delayed nodes)"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":288,"cache_read_input_tokens":34698,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":288},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c7af558-bf73-44d4-a74b-4537dca6c47c","uuid":"a45fcad6-0f50-45a6-8b9a-dc25ebe1c9b3","request_id":"req_011CcMYbwivYNvXfDu7JHy3V"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01ReRYb4MZ6TG9tMz5zp6q65","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_014phEXW9qzAFU6as5Fgt5U5","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/mydata/karma/runs/examples-rerererun/mongodb-rollback-rehearsal-20260624_053532/stages/stage_1/rollback.sh","content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Revert the mongodb replica set from its current non-default configuration\n# back to MongoDB 6.0 defaults.\n#\n# Non-default settings being reverted:\n#   systemLog.verbosity                          1      → 0      (MongoDB default)\n#   operationProfiling.mode                      slowOp → off    (MongoDB default)\n#   operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs         200    → 100    (MongoDB default)\n#   storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor  zlib → snappy  (WiredTiger default)\n#\n# Approach:\n#   Step 1 – Patch the mongod-config ConfigMap so newly-started pods use defaults.\n#   Step 2 – Push the runtime-settable changes (verbosity, profiling) to each\n#            running replica member immediately via mongosh, so they take effect\n#            without waiting for a pod restart.\n#   Step 3 – Rolling restart of the StatefulSet so all pods reload the config\n#            file and pick up the journalCompressor change (not runtime-settable).\n#\n# DO NOT execute this script while the cluster still depends on these settings.\n\nset -euo pipefail\n\nNAMESPACE=\"mongodb\"\nSTATEFULSET=\"mongodb-replica\"\nCONFIGMAP=\"mongod-config\"\nSECRET=\"admin-user-password\"\nAUTH_DB=\"admin\"\nADMIN_USER=\"admin-user\"\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Retrieve admin credentials from the existing Secret.\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\nADMIN_PASSWORD=$(kubectl -n \"$NAMESPACE\" get secret \"$SECRET\" \\\n  -o jsonpath='{.data.password}' | base64 -d)\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 1: Patch mongod-config ConfigMap.\n#   Removes: systemLog.verbosity, operationProfiling block.\n#   Reverts: journalCompressor zlib → snappy.\n#   Retains: all structural/required settings (dbPath, net, replication, security).\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\necho \"==> Step 1: Patching ConfigMap '${CONFIGMAP}' to revert to defaults...\"\n\nTMPCONF=$(mktemp /tmp/mongod-default.conf.XXXXXX)\ncat > \"$TMPCONF\" <<'EOF'\nstorage:\n  dbPath: /data/db\n  wiredTiger:\n    engineConfig:\n      journalCompressor: snappy\nnet:\n  bindIpAll: true\nreplication:\n  replSetName: mongodb-replica\nsecurity:\n  authorization: enabled\n  keyFile: /etc/mongo-keyfile/keyfile\nEOF\n\nkubectl -n \"$NAMESPACE\" create configmap \"$CONFIGMAP\" \\\n  --from-file=mongod.conf=\"$TMPCONF\" \\\n  --dry-run=client -o yaml | kubectl apply -f -\n\nrm -f \"$TMPCONF\"\necho \"    ConfigMap '${CONFIGMAP}' updated.\"\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 2: Apply runtime-settable resets to every live replica member.\n#   - logComponentVerbosity → 0 (was 1)\n#   - profilingLevel         → 0 / off, slowms → 100 ms (was slowOp / 200 ms)\n# These take effect immediately without a pod restart.\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\necho \"==> Step 2: Resetting runtime parameters on each pod...\"\n\nPODS=$(kubectl -n \"$NAMESPACE\" get pods -l \"app=${STATEFULSET}\" \\\n  -o jsonpath='{range .items[*]}{.metadata.name}{\"\\n\"}{end}')\n\nfor pod in $PODS; do\n  echo \"    -> ${pod}\"\n  kubectl -n \"$NAMESPACE\" exec \"$pod\" -- mongosh --quiet \\\n    -u \"$ADMIN_USER\" -p \"$ADMIN_PASSWORD\" \\\n    --authenticationDatabase \"$AUTH_DB\" \\\n    --eval '\n      db.adminCommand({ setParameter: 1, logComponentVerbosity: { verbosity: 0 } });\n      db.setProfilingLevel(0, { slowms: 100 });\n      print(\"  verbosity=0  profiling=off  slowms=100\");\n    '\ndone\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Step 3: Rolling restart so every pod reloads the updated config file.\n# Required for the journalCompressor change; WiredTiger reads it only at\n# startup. The StatefulSet rolling update strategy restarts one pod at a\n# time, waiting for it to be Ready before proceeding to the next.\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\necho \"==> Step 3: Rolling restart of StatefulSet '${STATEFULSET}'...\"\nkubectl -n \"$NAMESPACE\" rollout restart statefulset/\"$STATEFULSET\"\nkubectl -n \"$NAMESPACE\" rollout status statefulset/\"$STATEFULSET\" --timeout=300s\n\necho \"\"\necho \"==> Rollback complete.\"\necho \"\"\necho \"Verify with:\"\necho \"\"\necho \"  # Log verbosity (expect: verbosity: 0)\"\necho \"  kubectl -n ${NAMESPACE} exec mongodb-replica-0 -- \\\\\"\necho \"    mongosh --quiet -u ${ADMIN_USER} -p '<password>' \\\\\"\necho \"    --authenticationDatabase admin \\\\\"\necho \"    --eval 'db.adminCommand({getParameter:1, logComponentVerbosity:1})'\"\necho \"\"\necho \"  # Profiling status (expect: was: 0, slowms: 100)\"\necho \"  kubectl -n ${NAMESPACE} exec mongodb-replica-0 -- \\\\\"\necho \"    mongosh --quiet -u ${ADMIN_USER} -p '<password>' \\\\\"\necho \"    --authenticationDatabase admin \\\\\"\necho \"    --eval 'db.getProfilingStatus()'\"\necho \"\"\necho \"  # ConfigMap (expect: journalCompressor: snappy, no operationProfiling/systemLog blocks)\"\necho \"  kubectl -n ${NAMESPACE} get configmap ${CONFIGMAP} -o yaml\"\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":288,"cache_read_input_tokens":34698,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":288},"output_tokens":20,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c7af558-bf73-44d4-a74b-4537dca6c47c","uuid":"754289c4-9fc9-4978-bb6f-166c478ebd9f","request_id":"req_011CcMYbwivYNvXfDu7JHy3V"}
