{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01SL42ipBqxsWuGUaginprr4","type":"tool_result","content":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Revert the mongodb replica set from its current non-default configuration\n# back to MongoDB 6.0 defaults.\n#\n# Non-default settings being reverted:\n#   systemLog.verbosity                          1      → 0      (MongoDB default)\n#   operationProfiling.mode                      slowOp → off    (MongoDB default)\n#   operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs         200    → 100    (MongoDB default)\n#   storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor  zlib → snappy  (WiredTiger default)\n#\n# Approach:\n#   Step 1 – Patch the mongod-config ConfigMap so newly-started pods use defaults.\n#   Step 2 – Push the runtime-settable changes (verbosity, profiling) to each\n#            running replica member immediately via mongosh, so they take effect\n#            without waiting for a pod restart.\n#   Step 3 – Rolling restart of the StatefulSet so all pods reload the config\n#            file and pick up the journalCompressor change (not runtime-settable).\n#\n# DO NOT execute this script while the cluster still depends on these settings.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c7af558-bf73-44d4-a74b-4537dca6c47c","uuid":"664f5dc5-9058-4a35-8f70-aed5b08cefc8","timestamp":"2026-06-24T05:39:41.691Z","tool_use_result":{"stdout":"#!/usr/bin/env bash\n# Revert the mongodb replica set from its current non-default configuration\n# back to MongoDB 6.0 defaults.\n#\n# Non-default settings being reverted:\n#   systemLog.verbosity                          1      → 0      (MongoDB default)\n#   operationProfiling.mode                      slowOp → off    (MongoDB default)\n#   operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs         200    → 100    (MongoDB default)\n#   storage.wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor  zlib → snappy  (WiredTiger default)\n#\n# Approach:\n#   Step 1 – Patch the mongod-config ConfigMap so newly-started pods use defaults.\n#   Step 2 – Push the runtime-settable changes (verbosity, profiling) to each\n#            running replica member immediately via mongosh, so they take effect\n#            without waiting for a pod restart.\n#   Step 3 – Rolling restart of the StatefulSet so all pods reload the config\n#            file and pick up the journalCompressor change (not runtime-settable).\n#\n# DO NOT execute this script while the cluster still depends on these settings.","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01EhhQZBUp2Cw2BRTvBYhjZU","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The `rollback-rehearsal` ConfigMap is created. Here's a summary of what was done and why each choice was made:\n\n---\n\n**Non-default settings found (from `mongod-config` ConfigMap + live mongod inspection):**\n\n| Setting | Current | Default |\n|---|---|---|\n| `systemLog.verbosity` | `1` | `0` |\n| `operationProfiling.mode` | `slowOp` | `off` |\n| `operationProfiling.slowOpThresholdMs` | `200 ms` | `100 ms` |\n| `wiredTiger.engineConfig.journalCompressor` | `zlib` | `snappy` |\n\nThe replica set topology (`rs.conf()`) is entirely default — equal priority 1 members, no hidden nodes, no secondary delays — so nothing to revert there.\n\n---\n\n**Rollback script design (3 steps):**\n\n1. **Patch the ConfigMap** — rewrites `mongod.conf` with the structural settings kept intact (dbPath, net, replication, security) but all non-default blocks removed and `journalCompressor` reverted to `snappy`.\n\n2. **Runtime resets via mongosh on each pod** — verbosity and profiling can be changed without a restart via `setParameter` / `setProfilingLevel`. Doing this immediately means there's no window where the live cluster keeps the old settings while waiting for the rolling restart.\n\n3. **Rolling restart of the StatefulSet** — the `journalCompressor` is a WiredTiger startup parameter; it cannot be changed at runtime. The StatefulSet rolling update restarts one pod at a time, waiting for Ready before moving to the next, so the replica set stays available throughout.\n\nThe live cluster was not touched — the ConfigMap holding the rollback script is a new object (`rollback-rehearsal`), separate from the operational `mongod-config`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":406,"cache_read_input_tokens":41129,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":406},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"9c7af558-bf73-44d4-a74b-4537dca6c47c","uuid":"74a71df4-99aa-411e-ab99-c4b40f4b9a2f","request_id":"req_011CcMYhuD2dQniDNsteNbVM"}
